com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.venues

Class VenuesRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<T>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.PaginatedRequestExecutor<Venues>
        • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.venues.VenuesRequestExecutor

  • public class VenuesRequestExecutor
extends PaginatedRequestExecutor<Venues>
    Request executor provided by VenuesApi. Use this class if you want to fetch venues through fluent API in chained fashion, for example: 
       
   KontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloudFactory.create();
   Venues venues = kontaktCloud.venues().fetch()
      .managerIds(managerIDs)
      .startIndex(5)
      .maxResult(10)
      .execute();
